quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
40,59,"The Hour will indeed come; there is no doubt about that. Yet most people do not believe. {1}",footnotes:1:This is the absolute assertion about the occurrence of the Hereafter
40,60,"Your {1} Lord said: “Pray to Me, and I will accept your prayers. {2} Surely those who wax too proud to worship Me shall enter Hell, utterly abased.” {3}",footnotes:1:After the Hereafter
40,61,"Allah it is Who made the night so that you may seek repose in it, and made the day radiant. Surely Allah is Most Bounteous to people; but most people do not give thanks. {1}",footnotes:1:This verse comprises two important themes: First
40,62,"Allah (Who bestowed all these favours upon you) is your Lord, the Creator of everything. There is no god but He. {1} Whence are you, then, being led astray? {2}",footnotes:1:That is
40,63,"Thus it is only those who had denied Allah's Signs that were led astray. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
40,64,"Allah it is Who made the earth a dwelling place for you {1} and made the sky a canopy, {2} Who shaped you � and shaped you exceedingly well � and gave you good things as sustenance. {3} That is Allah, your Lord; blessed be Allah, the Lord of the Universe.",footnotes:1:For explanation
40,65,"He is the Ever-Living: {1} there is no god but He. So call upon Him, consecrating to Him all your devotion. {2} All praise and thanks be to Allah, the Lord of the whole Universe. {3}",footnotes:1:For explanation
40,66,"Say, (O Prophet): “I have been forbidden to worship those beside Allah whom you call upon. {1} (How can I worship any beside Allah) when clear Signs have come to me from my Lord and I have been commanded to surrender to Allah, the Lord of the Universe?”",footnotes:1:Here again ibadat (worship) and dua (prayer) have been used as synonyms.
